hopobject.body: Gloomy tales imaginehealthproducts.com There has been a steady rise in durable goods orders since the “end” of the recession, but it appears that the rise is over. Since the last quarter of 2011, durable goods sales have become stuck in a pretty tight range save for one outlier each to the upside and downside, as indicated by the red lines. While these numbers aren’t awful, they aren’t great either. Just like the rest of the economy, future performance in this sector will be meh.
